cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a novel solution to address the issue of noisy and low-quality images in set-based person re-identification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves feature learning and attention mechanisms, which are common in machine learning, particularly in deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also uses multiple datasets to evaluate the proposed method, which falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves the use of ID information to measure the quality of images, which is related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
